The paper deals with face anti-spoofing, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed method involves a novel Deep Tree Network (DTN), which is a machine learning model, indicating the relevance of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses various types of spoof attacks, which fall under the category of cybersecurity (cs.CR). The proposed method involves routing data samples to the most similar spoof cluster, which involves similarity measures and clustering techniques (cs.MM). Finally, the paper involves unsupervised learning, which is a subfield of artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
